Tozer (1901), ^Inf~. 34.59-60                     Doc 20 of 37, Screen  1

|Verso il graffiar~: `in comparison of the clawing.' Judas thus had the        
severest punishment, being torn by Lucifer's claws as well as by his teeth.    
|brulla~: `bare'; in Inf. xvi. 30 the form is ^brollo.~                        
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
                                                                               
